newsitem.title: FRANCE: Algeria passes on 100,000 T wheat import tender.
newsitem.headline: Algeria passes on 100,000 T wheat import tender.

text.p: Algeria has passed on offers in a tender it launched last Sunday for the purchase of 100,000 tonnes of milling wheat, European grain traders said on Thursday.
"Algeria passed on offers because they were too highly-priced," one trader said.
Algeria was seeking 100,000 tonnes of French, Argentine or U.S. milling wheat, or any combination of the three, for shipment in February and March.
Last week Algeria bought 50,000 tonnes of French wheat for January shipment at $172.50 per tonne, including freight and the cost of a Coface export credit, traders said.
